-- Harmony Gold Halts Operations at Tshepong After Death of Worker on Oct. 4
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 2010-10-06T06:27:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/harmony-gold-halts-operations-at-tshepong-after-death-of-worker-on-oct-4.html
Harmony Gold Mining Ltd. said it has
halted operations at its Tshepong mine in South Africa after a
fatal accident on Oct. 4.  Government safety inspectors may visit the site today,
spokeswoman Marian van der Walt said in an e-mailed response to
questions today. Lost production per day may amount to between
20 kilograms and 25 kilograms, she said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  